    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>cauliflower</strong>\u00a0into florets and add them to a baking tray</p><p>Drizzle\u00a0the <strong>florets</strong> with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 35-40 min or until the cauliflower is starting to turn brown and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the cauliflower is cooking, peel and dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat\u00a0a pot\u00a0with a lid with a large drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced\u00a0onion</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>sultanas</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 3 min or until the onion has softened slightly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>\u00a0to the pot and stir to coat the grains in oil</p><p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>\u00a0and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving - this is your <strong>spiced rice pilaf</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,\u00a0peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped\u00a0ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong> and <strong>most</strong> of the <strong>chopped\u00a0coriander</strong>\u00a0to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span>\u00a0of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and blitz until blended and smooth</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add\u00a0the<strong> ground almonds</strong> and <strong>coconut\u00a0yoghurt</strong>\u00a0with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>\u00a0to the <strong>food processor</strong> and blitz again into a thick paste \u2013 this is your <strong>fresh chutney</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>spiced rice pilaf</strong> with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-roast-cauliflower-with-spiced-rice-pilaf/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve\u00a0the <strong>roast</strong> <strong>cauliflower</strong> over the <strong>spiced rice</strong> <strong>pilaf</strong> with the <strong>fresh chutney</strong> dotted around</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
